    evidence: "Continuation resumed on PR #536: first preserve and verify inherited bot fixes, run a fresh repo-wide audit-boundary inventory, close any remaining core CLI/SDK audit surfaces, run focused/full/package/temp-project gates, publish the new head, then complete thread-aware bot acknowledgement and current-head CI convergence before merge."
body: "## Continuation closeout plan (2026-07-13)\n\n1. Inventory the entire current diff and every PR review/thread/check, preserving inherited uncommitted bot fixes.\n2. Run a repo-wide semantic audit-boundary sweep across src, SDK exports/contracts, MCP schemas, completion/help/guidance, docs, tests, package manifests, and generated fixtures; classify legitimate generic governance/history uses versus audit functionality that must move.\n3. Implement every remaining boundary correction inside packages/pm-governance-audit, with bare-core negative assertions and installed-package parity assertions.\n4. Run focused tests, contracts/snapshots, lint/static/token gates, full coverage/release gates, and an isolated installed-package temp-project proof.\n5. Record files/docs/tests and evidence in pm-rxp1, regenerate the package-owned changelog only after the final tracker mutation, commit with detailed lineage, and push PR #536.\n6. Trigger all configured AI reviewers on the pushed head, wait once for the complete review/check window (no polling), inventory all top-level reviews and inline threads, react according to usefulness, reply inline with disposition/evidence, resolve addressed threads, and repeat after every pushed fix.\n7. Re-read all edited/new comments and reactions, confirm all required GitHub checks are green on the exact head, merge, return to main, and verify merged-head health.\n\nNo core audit-named command, flag, public SDK symbol/type, MCP parameter, completion/help contract, or audit execution path is acceptable. Generic ownership enforcement, validate/health governance, and history-integrity semantics remain core only where they are not audit package functionality."
